paragraphs.text:
%sh

wget https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/3136860/Crime_Data.csv
hdfs dfs -put Crime_Data.csv /tmp
head Crime_Data.csv

%pyspark

# let's confirm what version of Spark we're running
print sc.version
print sqlContext

result.msg:
root
 |-- CrimeDate: string (nullable = true)
 |-- CrimeCode: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Location: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Description: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Weapon: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Post: integer (nullable = true)
 |-- District: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Neighborhood: string (nullable = true)
 |-- Location 1: string (nullable = true)

paragraphs.text:
%pyspark

# Run this statement if you need to re-create the 'crimes' table in Hive
sqlContext.sql("DROP TABLE crimes")

%pyspark

data.registerTempTable("staging")
sqlContext.sql("CREATE TABLE crimes STORED AS ORC AS SELECT * FROM staging")
central_crimes = sqlContext.sql("SELECT * FROM crimes WHERE district = 'CENTRAL'")

print type(central_crimes)
central_crimes.show()

%sql

select Neighborhood, Weapon, count(*) cnt from crimes
   group by Neighborhood, Weapon order by cnt desc
